  "answer": "**I could not find this specific couplet in the Falsafa corpus.**\n\nMirza Ghalib's *Diwan-e-Ghalib* is included (239 chapters of ghazals in English translation), and it frequently contrasts religious piety with wine-drinking ecstasy—e.g., preachers (*wa'iz*) scorning the tavern while the poet celebrates love's intoxicating \"wine\" (*mai/sharaab*) near mosques (*masjid*) or the Qibla.[^1][^2][^3] However, no verse matches your description of a mosque preacher's (*wa'iz/pandit/mullah*) cup (*jaam/paimana*) overflowing upon wine's arrival. Searches for key phrases across the corpus (including \"preacher\", \"mosque\", \"cup\", \"wine\", \"overflows\") yielded them separately, often in Iqbal or others, but never combined as stated.[^4]\n\nThe corpus covers 37 works; this phrasing may be a paraphrase, from another Ghalib collection, or outside our holdings. If you have more details (e.g., Urdu matla or ghazal number), I can search further.\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [ch. 131, p-36fb2c](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/131-masjid-ke-zer-e-saaya-kharabaat-chahiye/translation/#p-36fb2c).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [ch. 70, p-408c0c](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/70-hazaaron-khwahishein-aisi-ke-har-khwahish-pe-dam-n/translation/#p-408c0c).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [ch. 130, p-55e3af](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/130-manzoor-thi-yeh-shakl-tajalli-ko-noor-ki/translation/#p-55e3af).\n\n[^4]: E.g., Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, [ch. 9, p-dce5e7](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/09-majnoon-ne-sheher-chhora-to-sehra-bhi-chhor-de/translation/#p-dce5e7) (preacher on wine as sin).",
